properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Due to damaged bridge - CHARLEYONG/TOMBOYE Charleyong Bridge and Nerriga Road between Oallen Road, Oallen AND Braidwood
properties.otherAdvice:
This bridge is closed until further notice whilst repairs are undertaken. 

Residents will be permitted past closure points but cannot travel across the bridge.
properties.diversions:
The primary detour route (vehicles under 15 tonnes) is via Oallen Rd, Sandy Point Rd, Cullala Rd, Lumley Rd, Braidwood Rd and Kings Hwy, in both directions, adding around 35 minutes travel time.  

*Note Charleys Forrest Rd is also closed and cannot be used as a detour route.

Heavy vehicles should use the Kings Hwy, or other approved routes depending on their load limit restriction.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Oversize vehicle - BERRY TO BOMADERRY Princes Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Motorists are advised of an oversized delivery of bridge girders, for the Princes Hwy upgrade, which will be delivered in the early hours to minimise the impact on traffic. The 12 girders are 31m long, 2.1m wide and weigh approximately 50 tonnes each.

Police and escort vehicles will control traffic along the route and implement lane and side street closures, as required, to allow safe passage for the oversize truck to pass. Motorists are advised to drive to the conditions and follow the directions of signs and traffic control.
